Class ProfessorServiceImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.purdue.cs.encourse.service.impl.ProfessorServiceImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ProfessorService

    @Service(value="ProfessorService")
public class ProfessorServiceImpl
extends Object
implements ProfessorService
    Contains implementations for all services which are used by professors for managing a class Primarily used by endpoints called for professors
    Author:
    William Jordan Reed, reed226@purdue.edu

                          String courseID,

                          String semester,
                          @NonNull
                          String projectName,
                          String repoName,
                          String startDate,
                          String dueDate,
                          int testRate)
        Adds a new project to the database
        Specified by:
        addProject in interface ProfessorService
        Parameters:
        courseID - Identifier for course that is associated with the project
        semester - Semester that the project is assigned
        projectName - Name of the project for display purposes
        repoName - Name of the remote repository to clone
        startDate - Date that project will start for students
        dueDate - Date that project will be due for students
        testRate - Rate at which project will be pulled, tested, and analyzed automatically testRate is currently not used since automatic loop is run as often as possible
        Returns:
        The object representing the created project
